  {
    "title": "The power of daily learning",
    "date": "2026-01-12",
    "slug": "daily-learning",
    "category": "life",
    "tags": [],
    "content": "<p>Starting a TIL habit is about more than just documenting knowledge - it&#39;s about building a mindset of continuous growth.</p>\n<h2>Why Daily Learning Matters</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Compounding</strong> - Small learnings add up over time</li>\n<li><strong>Reflection</strong> - Writing forces you to understand deeply</li>\n<li><strong>Reference</strong> - Your future self will thank you</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>The Process</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Notice something new or interesting</li>\n<li>Take a moment to understand it</li>\n<li>Write it down in your own words</li>\n<li>Share it (optional but powerful)</li>\n</ol>\n<blockquote>\n<p>&quot;The best time to plant a tree was 20 years ago. The second best time is now.&quot;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Starting small is fine. Even one sentence counts. The habit matters more than the volume.</p>\n<h2>Making It Stick</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Keep it simple - don&#39;t overcomplicate the format</li>\n<li>Be consistent - same time each day helps</li>\n<li>Review periodically - look back at past months</li>\n</ul>\n",
    "navigation": {
