    "content": "<p>After years of failed attempts, I finally cracked the reading habit code.</p>\n<h2>The Mistake</h2>\n<p>I used to set ambitious goals: &quot;Read 52 books this year!&quot; Then I&#39;d burn out by February.</p>\n<h2>The Fix</h2>\n<p><strong>Read just 2 pages before bed.</strong> That&#39;s it.</p>\n<p>The magic is in the constraint:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>2 pages is so small you can&#39;t say no</li>\n<li>It happens at the same time daily (habit stacking)</li>\n<li>Most nights, you&#39;ll read more than 2 pages</li>\n<li>But you never <em>have</em> to</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Results</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>2024: 4 books (old approach)</li>\n<li>2025: 18 books (2-page rule)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Books That Changed My Thinking</h2>\n<ol>\n<li><em>Atomic Habits</em> - James Clear (meta, I know)</li>\n<li><em>The Mom Test</em> - Rob Fitzpatrick</li>\n<li><em>Staff Engineer</em> - Will Larson</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The goal isn&#39;t to read more. It&#39;s to <em>become</em> a reader. Identity precedes behavior.</p>\n",
